commit.message:
Tidy: Package header

Fixes #20.  Thanks to @benjaminor for reporting.

Fix: (ts-human-format-duration) Previous fix

The fix applied previously was testing the value of SECONDS after it
was bound to the plist' SECONDS :value, which can be 0 even if the
SECONDS passed to the function is non-zero.  The tests added didn't
catch this, because they tested with values that ts-human-duration
returned 0 :SECONDS for.  Oops.

Released as 0.2.2.

Test: (ts-format) Test additional timezone

To help avoid problems with the test machine's time zone affecting
results.

Change: (ts-fill) Add ZONE argument

Will help with testing ts-fill, see
<https://github.com/alphapapa/ts.el/issues/18> (though this argument
should have been added originally).

Tests: Add ts-fill

This may fail on Emacs 28.0.50.  See
<https://github.com/alphapapa/ts.el/issues/18>.

Tests: Fix ts-update

Thanks to Kisaragi Hiu (@kisaragi-hiu).

Tests: Fix ideal value for leap year length in seconds being off

Although the test doesn't support leap seconds, a normal leap year
should still be 31622400 seconds.

    (* 60 60 24 366) ;=> 31622400
